Problem Statement: Remove character
Problem Level: EASY
Problem Description:
Given a string and a character x. Write a function to remove all occurrences of x character from the given string.
Leave the string as it is, if the given character is not present in the string.
<br>
Input Format :
Line 1 : String S
Line 2 : Character c

Output Format :
Modified string

Constraints :
0 <= |S| <= 10^7
where |S| represents the length of string, S.

Sample Input 1:
welcome to coding ninjas
o

Sample Output 1:
welcme t cding ninjas

Sample Input 2:
Think of edge cases before submitting solutions
x

Sample Output 2:
Think of edge cases before submitting solutions

//Solution


class Solution {

    static String removeAllOccurrencesOfChar(String input, char c) {
        // Write your code here
        
    String res="";
        for(int i=0;i<input.length();i++){
            if(input.charAt(i)!=c){
                res=res+input.charAt(i);
            }
        }
